               <p>Bedouin-type dialect</p>
            </div>
            <div type="general">
               <p xml:space="preserve">Sidi Shil is a mountainous region in the north of the Tunisian governorate of Kasserine, close to the town of Thala. While summers are hot and dry, the wintertime brings very cold temperatures and even large amounts of snow. Tribal communities predominate the region. Most inhabitants are of Bedouin origin and live their lives in accordance with tradition.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="researchHistory">
               <p xml:space="preserve">To the best of our knowledge hitherto no research has been done on the dialect of Sidi Shil, however this dialect is linguistically investigated within the TUNOCENT project.</p>
            </div>
